Form Element - Drop-down Menu - cml:select

- Renders a drop-down menu
- Accepts all Common Attributes

[code]
<cml:select label="Sample select box:"> 
<cml:option label="Option 1" /> 
<cml:option label="Option 2" /> 
<cml:option label="Option 3" /> 
</cml:select>
[/code]

<img src="sample_select.png" />

The [code]<cml:option />[/code] children elements accept the following attributes:

[code]label[/code]
The visible label for the option. This is different than the parent [code]<cml:select>[/code] element's "label" attribute, which is the label for the entire drop-down menu.

[code]value[/code]
The value that gets submitted if the contributor selects the corresponding option. If this isn't present, the value of the "label" attribute is submitted.